# Story Authoring Rules

When creating or editing files in `docs/stories/`:

## Required Frontmatter

```yaml
---
id: STORY-NNN
title: "Descriptive title"
status: {{STATUS_VALUES_FIRST}}
owner: contributor-name
priority: medium
acceptance:
  - "Criterion 1"
updated_at: YYYY-MM-DD
---
```

## Rules

- Story IDs are sequential (`STORY-001`, `STORY-002`, ...) and never reused
- Status must be one of: {{STATUS_VALUES}}
- Completed stories go to `docs/stories/archive/` — never delete
- Link to parent spec via `spec: SPEC-XXX-NNN` when applicable
- Acceptance criteria use Markdown checkboxes: `- [ ] Criterion`
- If editing as an AI agent, set `locked_by` and `locked_at` in frontmatter
